Hi all, I don't suppose anyone here would know why choice fields in custom modules at times return 'module' as a default value despite a default value being explicitly set?
Here is a small snippet:
```&lt;section class="{{ module.color.background_color }} py-10 py-sm-7 py-md-9"&gt;
  {% if module.type == 'module' %}hello world{% endif %} &lt;!-- testing --&gt;
  &lt;div class="{% if module.type == 'video' %}video-carousel{% endif %} {% if module.type == 'image' %}image-carousel{% endif %}"&gt;
  ...```
The default in 'module.color.background_color' works fine but 'module.type' returns 'module' unless user selects in the content editor, another option (video in this case) and then selects the image option again.
